-- CANADA STOCKS-TSX drops as TD, energy stocks dive
-- By John Tilak
-- Thu Dec 04, 2014 04:10PM EST
-- None



TORONTO, Dec 4 (Reuters) - Canada's main stock index recorded its biggest single-day drop in about 18 months on Thursday as weakness in the price of oil fueled a selloff in the energy sector and Toronto-Dominion Bank <TD.TO> fell after the lender reported quarterly results.

